# ============================================================================
# SECURITY — this repo is PUBLIC on GitHub. Never let credentials or browser
# state get committed. Defense-in-depth: even if `git add -A` is run by
# mistake, these patterns keep secrets out. (Also enforced by .githooks/pre-commit.)
# ============================================================================

# Headless-Chrome bot profiles (testing/) — browser profiles can hold cookies,
# "Login Data", and cached auth. They are throwaway (local file:// game only)
# and MUST NOT be published. Ignore the profile dirs; keep the test CODE.
testing/_chromeprofile/
testing/_chromeprofile_cdp/
testing/frames/
**/_chromeprofile*/
**/Default/Cookies
**/Default/Login Data
**/Default/Web Data

# Secret / credential files — never commit any of these
*.env
.env*
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
*.keystore
id_rsa*
id_ed25519*
*credential*
*secret*
*.secrets
secrets.*
settings.local.json
.claude/
.npmrc
.netrc
service-account*.json
gcp-*.json
aws-credentials*
*.token
token.txt
